  "original_title": "6 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba9\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbf \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Indefinite strike demanding release of 6 fishermen",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Rameswaram fishermen are on an indefinite strike demanding the release of 6 fishermen and the power boat in Sri Lankan jail.",
        "On the 21st, fishermen in more than 500 boats went out to sea from Rameswaram fishing port. They were fishing between Dhanushkodi-Talaimannar. At that time, the Sri Lankan Navy patrolling the area arrested a barge and 6 fishermen including Anthony and Ajith, who were fishing across the border, and imprisoned them in Sri Lanka's Vavunia jail.",
        "Subsequently, in the fishermen's consultation meeting held yesterday in Rameswaram, it was decided to go on an indefinite strike from yesterday and protest at Rameswaram bus station today (July 24) demanding the release of the 6 fishermen arrested by the Sri Lankan Navy and the barge. According to this, more than 700 barges were anchored yesterday in Rameswaram port without going for fishing. Fishermen said that this would result in a loss of revenue of more than Rs.5 crore per day."
      ],
